Definition: tending to soothe or tranquilize
Example: valium has a tranquilizing effect; took a hot drink with sedative properties before going to bed
Synonyms: noun, artifact, attribute, ataraxia, ataraxic, sedative, verb, body, sedate, tranquilizing, tranquillizing, tranquilising, tranquillising, tending, to, soothe, or, tranquilize, valium, has, a, effect, took, hot, drink, with, properties, before, going, bed
Category: adj.all
